<div id="review_148563237" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/148563237" />
    <a title="Niki" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/795716-niki"><img alt="Niki" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1477977854p2/795716.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/148563237?book_show_action=true">Feb 16, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Niki" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Niki" href="/user/show/795716-niki">Niki</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer148563237" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12620248846692499678">I once had a good friend of mine tease me in college for wanting a &quot;white picket fence.&quot; I was dating around looking for &quot;the one&quot;. I was offended at first, but then realized that IS what I wanted and was looking for. Even though there is no &quot;white picket fence&quot; in my yard, I feel like I have the life I always dreamed of. Of course it has it&apos;s challenges, but I feel so blessed, especially to have found someone so wonderful to share my life with.<br/><br/>You may wonder why I am saying all this in a book r</span>
  <span id="freeText12620248846692499678" style="display:none">I once had a good friend of mine tease me in college for wanting a "white picket fence." I was dating around looking for "the one". I was offended at first, but then realized that IS what I wanted and was looking for. Even though there is no "white picket fence" in my yard, I feel like I have the life I always dreamed of. Of course it has it's challenges, but I feel so blessed, especially to have found someone so wonderful to share my life with.<br /><br />You may wonder why I am saying all this in a book review, but these books have helped me remember what is most important in life. It's a good old fashioned love story about two kids starting out their lives together and discovering their purpose in life. <br /><br />I know these books are very "rose-colored glasses" and usually I don't like books where everything seems to work out. There is some very sad things in these books, but overall it is very positive. But I realize, that is okay to want and hope for positive things. I think the world has made us all so cynical and feel like it's not okay to see the world through "rose-colored lenses". I have been so uplifted by these books and love hearing the story of a tiny, old fashioned town in Pennsylvania where the community still loves and cares for each other like family. It has helped me realize the most important things in my life to be grateful for. And, it's okay to be happy and enjoy life! <br /><br />P.S. Thanks to my in-laws for giving us these books for Christmas! </span>
  <a data-text-id="12620248846692499678" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


