<div id="review_104265831" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/104265831" />
    <a title="Carole" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/900891-carole"><img alt="Carole" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/104265831?book_show_action=true">May 25, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Carole" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Carole" href="/user/show/900891-carole">Carole</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title=" " href="/book/show/8303344-discovering-isaac">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer104265831" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5401688689393073356">I liked this book less than Volume I. The novelty of the format had worn off somewhat, and the messages passed on from Isaac, the potter, were more heavyhanded. Behunin could still use a more professional editor and proofreader.<br/><br/>But having said that, I will probably purchase and read Vol. 3. This is a young, local author, who has turned to writing because arthritis is curtailing his making a living as a potter.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


